PrecisOrder (a) approving a "SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT" between the Federal Crown, the Province of British Columbia and the SONGHEES INDIAN BAND which is designed to resolve and extinguish a specific claim pertaining to the cutting-off in 1924 of some 0.5 acres of land from its reserve, more particularly, Halkett Island in Victoria Harbour, and (b) setting apart that island for the use and benefit of the Band as (Deadman's) HALKETT ISLAND INDIAN RESERVE NO. 2.
